SIMPLE: standoff
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: standoff
<hw>stand"off</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A situation in a
contest in which the winner is undecided; a draw or stalemate.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> draw; tie; stalemate; deadlock</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A successful stand.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> repulsion, repelling</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Something that serves to keep one object at a
distance from another, such as a prop attached to the top of a ladder to
keep it from leaning directly against the vertical surface which
supports it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>standoff</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: standoff
<hw>stand"off</hw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Serving to keep two objects or
parts of a machine separated; <as>as, a <ex>standoff</ex>
insulator</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>stand-offish</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>standoffish</ent>⟦br⟧
